    "summary": "Ph.D. in Experimental Physics at the Free University Amsterdam in 1993 (generation of soft X-ray radiation from laser-produced plasma sources).\nPart-time professor on XUV sources and optics at the MESA+ Institute for Nanotechnology at the University of Twente in 2005.\nHead of the Nanolayer Surface and Interface Physics department at the FOM-Institute for Plasma Physics Rijnhuizen (now FOM DIFFER) from 2006 to 2014.\nInitiated the Industrial Focus Group XUV Optics at MESA+ in 2012, a public-private thematic research consortium.\nChair and full professor of the Industrial Focus Group XUV Optics from 2013 to 2021.\nScience and valorisation advisor in the XUV Optics group as of 2021.\n\nPublished over 100 journal articles and over 30 patents.\nConducted numerous (inter)national science projects with academical and industrial partners.\nTransferred various XUV related processes to industry.\nReceived the FOM Valorization Prize in 2011.\n\nSpecialties: Extreme UV photolithography, XUV optics and multilayer coating technology, x-ray lithographic imaging, laser plasma XUV light sources",
